Document: navigation_debug_tools
Path: godot/tutorials/navigation/navigation_debug_tools.rst
Summary: How to enable and use navigation debug visualizations in Godot

Navigation debug visualizations are enabled by default in the editor. To visualize navigation meshes and connections during runtime, enable the **Visible Navigation** option in the editor's **Debug** menu. In Godot debug builds, this can also be controlled via NavigationServer singletons in scripts.

GDScript:
    NavigationServer2D.set_debug_enabled(false)
    NavigationServer3D.set_debug_enabled(true)

C#:
    NavigationServer2D.SetDebugEnabled(false);
    NavigationServer3D.SetDebugEnabled(true)

Note: Debug visualizations rely on Nodes in the SceneTree. If NavigationServer2D or NavigationServer3D APIs are used exclusively without SceneTree integration, changes will not be reflected in the debug navigation tools.
---CHUNK---
